Author:  MORRiS
Vol / Page:  162
Edition:
Quote:  <i>Goai ... </i>common name in southern island of New Zealand for<i> kowhai</i> (q.v.), of which it is a corruption. it is especially used of the timber of this tree, which is valuable for fencing. The change from K to G also took place in the <i>Otago</i>, formerly spelt <i>Otakou. </i>
